<webwork-reps version="2" webwork2_major_version="2" webwork2_minor_version="20" xml:id="extracted-section-solving-rational-equations-10-10-26" assembly-id="section-solving-rational-equations-10-10-26">
  <static seed="1461" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalEquations/solveRationalEquations61.pg">
    <statement><p>Solve the equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ {\frac{1}{t-8}-\frac{4}{t^{2}-8t}} = {{\frac{1}{6}}} }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="34" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left\{12,2\right\}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To get rid of fractions, we multiply each term in this equation by the common denominator, which is <m>{6t\mathopen{}\left(t-8\right)}</m> in this example.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \amp {\frac{1}{t-8}-\frac{4}{t^{2}-8t}} = {{\frac{1}{6}}} \\
   \amp {\frac{1}{t-8}-\frac{4}{t\mathopen{}\left(t-8\right)}} ={{\frac{1}{6}}} \\
   \amp {\frac{1}{t-8}\cdot 6t\mathopen{}\left(t-8\right)-\frac{4}{t\mathopen{}\left(t-8\right)}\cdot 6t\mathopen{}\left(t-8\right)} = {{\frac{1}{6}}\cdot 6t\mathopen{}\left(t-8\right)} \\
   \amp {6t-24} = {t\mathopen{}\left(t-8\right)} \\
   \amp {6t-24} = {t^{2}-8t} \\
   \amp {6t-24-t^{2}+8t} = 0 \\
   \amp {-t^{2}+14t-24} = 0 \\
   \amp {-\left(t^{2}-14t+24\right)} = 0 \\
   \amp -({t-12})({t-2}) =0 \\
   \amp {t-12}=0 \:\: or\:\: {t-2}=0 \\
   \amp t={12} \:\: or\:\: t={2}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p><alert>Checking</alert></p>
<p>We must check solutions when we solve rational equations. In the original equation, both denominators cannot be <m>0</m>. We set them to <m>0</m>, so we can find out what values to exclude from the solution set.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \amp t^2 - 8t = 0 \amp \;\amp  t - 8=0 \\
   \amp t(t - 8) =0 \amp \;\amp  t=8 \\
   \amp t=0 \:\:or\:\: t - 8=0 \\
   \amp t=0 \:\:or\:\: t=8
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>We must exclude <m>0</m> and <m>8</m> from the solution set. There is no conflict with those two solutions we got earlier, so the final solution are <m>t={12}</m> and <m>t={2}</m>.</p>
</solution>
